<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Leaf</emphasis>
collars often scabrous or hispidulous near the throat; ligules of middle cauline leaves 0.2-1.5 mm long, not decurrent, abaxially smooth or scabrous, upper margin scabrous or ciliolate or glabrous, apices truncate; sterile shoot blades frequently glabrous adaxially. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Spikelet</emphasis>
rachilla internodes smooth, glabrous; lemma keels and marginal veins smooth or sparingly scabrous, glabrous or sparsely short villous to softly puberulent; palea keels glabrous, between keels glabrous. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Lodicules</emphasis>
0.6-0.7 mm long, broadly lanceolate to ovate, with or without a brief lateral lobe from below the middle. 2 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">n</emphasis>
= 28, 28+II.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="24" pageNumber="25">The subspecies is endemic to southeastern Arizona, southwestern New Mexico, USA, and the northern Sierra Madre Occidental of Mexico (Chihuahua, Sonora).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
